31 March 2017 -- Note for users of Linux kernels older than 2.6.27

    If you are stuck with a kernel from July 2008 or earlier (2.6.26 or less),
    and you are using mdev, device scan wouldn't work correctly due to an
    incompatibility in /sys structure. You can work around it by reverting this
    0001-mdev-create-devices-from-sys-dev.patch patch in 1.26.x BusyBox sources.
    (You also probably need to plan migration to a less ancient kernel).


10 January 2017 -- BusyBox 1.26.2 (stable)

    Bug fix release. 1.26.2 has fixes for
        ash (redirect fds sometimes were not closed),
        module utilities and tcpsvd (build fixes),
        build system (IFUPDOWN_UDHCPC_CMD_OPTIONS option was not settable).


2 January 2017 -- BusyBox 1.26.1 (stable)

    Bug fix release. 1.26.1 has fixes for
        single-applet builds (all applets are verified to successfully build when 
        individually selected), a few tweaks to defconfig were made.
        Static binaries are available for downloads, with each individual applet
        enabled separately, as well as the binary with almost all applets selected,
        and helper binaries (ssl_helper for HTTPS wget support, index.cgi,
        post_upload.cgi and httpd_ssi for HTTP server).


